<P>
 SUSAN B. ANTHONY SLEPT HERE: A Guide to American Women's Landmarks by Lynn 
Sherr & Jurate Kazickas (Times Books: $18; 579 pp., illustrated). In this newly 
expanded edition, Sherr and Kazickas identify more than 2,000 sites associated 
with women's achievements, ranging from monuments to Betsy Ross, Eleanor 
Roosevelt and Gertrude Stein to the graves of vaudevillians Addie and Effie 
Cherry, once billed as "the world's worst sister act." Local points of interest 
include a mural honoring Biddy Mason, one of the founders of the African 
Methodist Episcopal Church, in downtown Los Angeles, and Dorsey High School, 
named for Susan Dorsey, the first female superintendent of schools in Los 
Angeles. 
