<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE REAL FIRST IN SPACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In your July 10-16 issue of TV Times, it is stated in the interview with Alan 
Shepard that he was the first man into space. That is incorrect. The Russian 
cosmonaut Yuri Gagarin became the first man to go into space -- a month before 
Shepard's flight -- on April 12, 1961, from Star City, Russia. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Savard, San Clemente 
</P>
