<P>
 CHITOSE OKASHIRO: Piano works by Schumann: Symphonic Etudes, Opus 13 and Opus 
Posthumous; "Arabeske."Mozart: Sonata in B-flat, K. 570. Pieces by Chopin, 
Scarlatti, Scriabin and Brahms. Pro Piano CD 224501. As Director of Artists and 
Repertoire for the company and co-producer of this disk, Okashiro has 
essentially provided a compilation of recital standards. The Japanese pianist 
approaches the material with discernible intelligence, but blankets it all with 
a Romantic bent. Still, the performances impress. They abound with subtle 
shadings and lively projection, all well-served by technical security and 
enhanced by a recording characterized by much -- almost excessive -- 
reverberation. SUSAN BLISS 
