JULIE, JULIE, JULIE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I am a Brit in L.A., and your "Our Favorite Quote" on Page 2 caught my eye 
July 17.The actress's name was unfamiliar and I thought to myself, "Ah, a new 
British actress with exactly my thoughts on this town." 
</P>
<P>
 I turned to Page 24 to see who this actress was -- she's not a new actress at 
all. Her name is Julie Walters, not Rita . She played Rita in a movie. How 
could you make this glaring error? 
</P>
<P>
 I can only presume the proof-reader job is currently available and would 
therefore like to apply. 
</P>
<P>
 MAGGIE HICKERSON 
