<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; WARNING AGAINST RUSSIAN AIR TRAVEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The U.S. State Department is warning Americans not to travel within Russia on 
the many small airlines that have resulted from the breakup of Aeroflot. 
</P>
<P>
 In its new Consular Information Sheet on Russia, the department cited Russian 
airlines' "unpredictable schedules and difficult conditions, including 
deterioration of . . . maintenance, quality of service and overloading." 
</P>
<P>
 U.S. government officials were earlier warned to defer routine domestic air 
travel in the country and to seek alternate means of transportation when 
possible. 
</P>
<P>
 For a copy of the information sheet, call the State Department's Citizens 
Emergency Center, (202) 647-5225, or its automated fax service, (202) 647-3000. 
</P>
