<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE MATURE TRAVELER: THE OTHER SUNNY ESCAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HANK KOVELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Florida is among those states avidly courting the senior market as the 
following offers indicate: 
</P>
<P>
 * Palm Beach County on Florida's Atlantic coast is offering a massive coupon 
book with hundreds of offers, many of which are 2-for-1 deals including meals 
at restaurants, tours, cruises, theater tickets, sports such as golf, bowling, 
deep-sea fishing, scuba diving and water sports. Merchandise discounts of up to 
25% off are sometimes offered.Participating vendors will require proof of age 
over 55. For a free coupon book, call (800) 554-7256 or write to Palm Beach 
Visitor Bureau, 1555 Palm Beach Lakes Blvd. No. 204, West Palm Beach, Fla. 
33401. 
</P>
<P>
 * The Miami River Inn adjacent to downtown Miami is a restored B&B listed in 
the National Register of Historic Places. It has 38 rooms with private bath, 
cable TV, air-conditioning and includes daily continental breakfast. Travelers 
over 50 receive a $50 per room rate. Offer is valid until Sept. 30. Call (305) 
325-0045 or write to Miami River Inn, 118 S.W. South River Drive, Miami, Fla. 
33130. 
</P>
<P>
 In Jacksonville: 
</P>
<P>
 * The oceanfront Sea Turtle Inn has access to several kinds of water sports, 
tourist attractions, restaurants and shopping. Seniors over age 65 receive 
discounts that average $10 per room on accommodations that range from $89 to 
$109 Sunday through Thursday. Call (800) 874-6000. 
</P>
<P>
 In Tampa: 
</P>
<P>
 * Ramada Airport Hotel offers a 25% discount off their $69 corporate rate for 
a net of $52 for guests over age 60. Call (800) 228-2828. 
</P>
<P>
 * Tampa's Busch Gardens Holiday Inn grants a 10% discount year-round for 
guests over age 55. An $82 standard room becomes $73.80 and a poolside room at 
$92 becomes $82.80. Call (800) 465-4329. 
</P>
