<P>
SWEET MEMORIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ann Salmeron's "Churros and Chocolate" (June 12) had our mouths 
watering.Eating hot churros dipped in chocolate pudding is one of life's early 
morning pleasures -- and one that became a habit for us during a month's visit 
to Spain. The so-called churros that are sugar coated and kept warm in a cart 
here have nothing to do with Spain's delectable treats. Is there anyplace in 
Los Angeles where you can enjoy the real thing? 
</P>
<P>
