<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOW FAT MEMORIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Carol Isaak Barden's well-written article, "Low Fat Desert" (July 3), brought 
back many memories of when I discovered Rancho La Puerta in the early '60s. 
</P>
<P>
 A friend had recommended the ranch as an ideal place for a rest.After spending 
a week there, I was totally addicted. For $125 a week, per person, we got a 
small cottage with a fireplace, three good meals (mostly vegetarian), one 
massage and a facial a day. 
</P>
<P>
 Soon after, we started going down for weekends whenever we could. Those 
weekends were not as restful as they should have been, as we spent many 
Saturday evenings at the local pub, sneaking back in long past curfew. They 
have since built a guarded gate and their rates have been inflated to the point 
of making it available only to the super-rich. Sad! 
</P>
<P>
 SIMONNE REYNOLDS, Santa Monica 
</P>
</TEXT>
