<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: VENTURA; BUS DRIVERS MATCH MANEUVERING SKILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It's just a little friendly competition among bus drivers -- a chance to test 
their skills at maneuvering a 35-foot bus through an obstacle course in record 
time. 
</P>
<P>
 Twenty South Coast Area Transit bus drivers will participate in the eighth 
annual Bus Roadeo, which gets under way at 9 a.m. today in the parking lot of 
San Buenaventura State Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 The drivers will be rated on their ability to maneuver a bus through a 
specially designed obstacle course during a timed race. They will also be 
required to take written tests and perform routine safety checks of their 
vehicles. 
</P>
<P>
 The winner of the SCAT Roadeo will travel to Boston in September to compete 
against drivers from across the United States and Canada. TRACY WILSON 
</P>
