<HEADLINE>
<P>
INS TEST HAD 2 WRONG ANSWERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Of the six sample questions from the INS Citizenship Examination ("How Well 
Would You Do?" July 18), two have incorrect answers. There are now 27 
amendments to the United States Constitution, and while the House of 
Representatives has 435 seats, Congress, which includes the House and the 
Senate, has 535 (plus five non-voting delegates, one each from the District of 
Columbia and four American territories). 
</P>
<P>
 I hope the people teaching the citizenship classes are doing a better job than 
the people writing the INS examination. 
</P>
<P>
 THOMAS A. CHAMBERS 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
