<P>
WEBBER, STARKS, RICHMOND JOIN MAGIC IN ALL-STAR GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS BAKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Forward Chris Webber of the Golden State Warriors, the NBA's rookie of the 
year, and All-Star guards John Starks of the New York Knicks, Mitch Richmond of 
the Sacramento Kings and Gary Payton of the Seattle SuperSonics will play in 
Magic Johnson's ninth annual Mid-Summer Night's Magic charity basketball game 
tonight at 7:30 at the Forum. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnson, who led the Lakers to five NBA titles, will lead the U.S. All-Stars 
against the California All-Stars led by Payton, University of California guard 
Jason Kidd, the second pick in the NBA draft, and Phoenix Sun forward Cedric 
Ceballos. 
</P>
