 Others who will play include Purdue forward Glenn Robinson, the top choice in 
the draft; Clipper guards Ron Harper and Pooh Richardson, Indiana Pacer guard 
Mark Jackson, Dallas Maverick forward Jamal Mashburn, Orlando Magic guard 
Anfernee Hardaway, Washington Bullet forward Don MacLean and Portland Trail 
Blazer forward Tracy Murray. 
</P>
<P>
 Billy Crystal and Arsenio Hall will be the coaches for the game, which 
benefits the United Negro College Fund. 
</P>
<P>
 The game will be preceded by a celebrity game at 6 p.m. with actors Tom Cruise 
and Malcolm Jamal Warner and rapper Hammer among those scheduled to 
participate. CHRIS BAKER 
