<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJOR LEAGUES; ROYALS WILL PLAY ON GRASS 
NEXT SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kauffman Stadium, home of the Kansas City Royals, will have a much different 
look next season. 
</P>
<P>
 Like nearby Arrowhead Stadium, home of the NFL's Chiefs, Kauffman Stadium will 
replace its artificial turf with natural grass for next season, along with 
moving fences in and lowering them from 12 feet to nine feet. 
</P>
<P>
 "By putting in grass, we needed to add some offense to the park, and the only 
way to do that was to move in the fences," Royal General Manager Herk Robinson 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 A Comiskey Park fan who fell from the bleachers Saturday while reaching for a 
home run hit by Chicago White Sox first baseman Frank Thomas received a scraped 
elbow and an autographed ball from the slugger. 
</P>
<P>
 The fan, whose name was not released, fell out of the bleachers and onto his 
back in the Seattle Mariners' bullpen and was taken out of the park on a 
stretcher. 
</P>
</TEXT>
