<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHITAKER DOMINATED IN GOODWILL FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lance Whitaker of Northridge, the country's top-ranked amateur super 
heavyweight who began boxing about two years ago, lost to Alexi Lezin of 
Russia, 17-0, Saturday in the gold-medal bout of the Goodwill Games in St. 
Petersburg, Russia. 
</P>
<P>
 The inexperienced Whitaker (29-4), 6-foot-8, 235 pounds, was no match for 
Lezin, losing to the three-time Russian national champion for the third time. 
</P>
<P>
 Lezin, a left-hander, continually befuddled Whitaker, beating him to the punch 
at almost every opportunity and preventing the American from using his height 
and weight advantages. 
</P>
<P>
 "He beat me, he beat me good," Whitaker said. "He was faster than me and I was 
about two seconds late with every punch I threw." 
</P>
</TEXT>
