<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEAMSTRESS SNIPS OFF HUSBAND'S PENIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A seamstress snipped off her husband's penis with a pair of scissors Saturday 
and said he deserved it. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm ready to face charges.I'm also ready to fight for my rights," Gina 
Espina, 21, said from a Manila city jail. "He deserved what I did to him 
because he has been abusing me for so long." 
</P>
<P>
 Espina said she had agreed to stay with her husband, Donald Jacolo, despite 
learning two years into their marriage that his first marriage had not been 
annulled. 
</P>
<P>
 She said that early Saturday, while her husband slept in a motel where they 
had checked in to discuss their marriage problems, she snipped off his penis 
and threw it onto the floor. 
</P>
<P>
 Jacolo woke up to find himself bleeding and called security to apprehend his 
wife. He immediately sought medical help to reattach his severed penis, but the 
doctors' efforts failed. 
</P>
<P>
 Jacolo told a local radio station later that he will press charges. 
</P>
