<TEXT>
<P>
 Italian President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro and Umberto Bossi, a key partner in the 
governing coalition, have thrown cold water on Prime Minister Silvio 
Berlusconi's efforts to distance himself from his vast business holdings. 
</P>
<P>
 Scalfaro said in a statement that while he appreciated Berlusconi's plan, 
constitutional restraints would probably prevent him from helping guarantee its 
success. 
</P>
<P>
 He said he would wait to take a stand on Berlusconi's proposal until a panel 
