<TEXT>
<P>
 Militiamen loyal to powerful Somali faction leader Mohammed Farah Aidid 
attacked and disarmed Zimbabwean U.N. peacekeepers stationed in the central 
town of Belet Huen, a U.N. military spokesman said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
