<P>
GREEN THUMB; GROWING STRAIGHT PLANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Take the time to rotate your houseplants regularly. If plants are turned 
one-quarter turn each time they are watered, they will grow straight. Otherwise 
they will have a tendency to bend toward their light source. 
</P>
