<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: RAMPART AREA; HUNDREDS EXPECTED FOR ANTI-CRIME MARCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 At least 2,500 people are expected to participate locally Tuesday evening in 
the first citywide observance of "National Night Out," joining in an anti-crime 
march throughout the Rampart area. 
</P>
<P>
 "What we're trying to do with this event is pretty much bring the L.A. area 
together," said Officer Webster Wong of the Rampart Division's community 
relations office. 
</P>
<P>
 Marchers will gather at 5:30 p.m. at six meeting points, eventually converging 
upon Rampart Division headquarters. There, Wong said, speakers and 
entertainment -- including a candlelight ceremony and fireworks -- will be 
featured. 
</P>
<P>
 The six meeting points are: 3rd Street and Kenmore Avenue; Willowbrook Avenue 
and Hoover Street; 7th and Alvarado streets; Beaudry Avenue and Temple Street; 
Vendome and Del Monte streets, and Beverly Boulevard and Vendome Street. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 485-4080. 
</P>
</TEXT>
