COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: MID-CITY; POLICE TO OPEN STOP-IN CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Police Department's Wilshire Division will open a police stop-in center 
Tuesday at 4012 Washington Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 The LAPD-Washington Square Stop-In Center will be used by police to complete 
administrative functions, take on-site reports, and provide general information 
and referrals. The center will also host Neighborhood Watch meetings and other 
community activities. 
</P>
<P>
 Ceremonies begin at 6:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 485-7992. 
</P>
