<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN HELD IN ALLEGED RAPE IN LA HABRA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 32-year-old was arrested on suspicion of rape Saturday morning, less than 2 
1/2 hours after he allegedly attacked a sleeping woman in her apartment, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Emanual Ascencio of La Habra was arrested by police officers, who saw he was 
driving a Chevrolet pickup that matched the description of a vehicle given by 
the victim's neighbors, Sgt. Kevin Raisch said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ascencio was stopped near Walnut Avenue and Whittier Boulevard, about a 
quarter mile from the home of the victim, who later identified Ascencio as her 
attacker, Raisch said. The woman did not know Ascencio, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspect was held in lieu of $50,000 bail, Raisch said. 
</P>
<P>
 The assault occurred at 8:30 a.m. after an intruder climbed through a 
screened, open kitchen window at the woman's home, police said. 
</P>
