<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE CALLED OVER BB GUN SHOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police said an unidentified man was seen shooting a gun that was later 
determined to be a BB gun from the roof of a storage warehouse across the 
street from the Winnetka Drive-In on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Several police cars and a police helicopter responded to the "sniper call" at 
about 5 p.m. on Winnetka and Praire avenues.Police closed off both streets for 
about half an hour, said Sgt. Mike Sonntag of the LAPD's Devonshire Division. 
</P>
<P>
 A person on a car phone called police to report seeing a man with brown hair 
shooting a gun from the warehouse roof, Sonntag said. Police searched the area 
and found a BB gun cartridge. He added that no arrests were made and no one was 
injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA073194-0400 </DOCNO>
